timing_path_ba...ax_paths_limit(25.10)  timing_path_ba...ax_paths_limit(25.10)

Name
       timing_path_based_exhaustive_max_paths_limit

Syntax
       timing_path_based_exhaustive_max_paths_limit <integer>

       Default: 2000000

       Specifies  the  maximum number of paths that can be internally analyzed
       during exhaustive path-based analysis (PBA).

       If the number of candidate paths during exhaustive PBA is greater  than
       the  specified  max paths limit, then the software will skip path-based
       analysis of these paths beyond this  limit.  The  paths  exceeding  the
       specified max paths limit will then be included as GBA in the final re-
       port output so that real violations are not missed.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

